      <description>&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyStart:02d10f05-4469-4c6e-bb9f-cb03efde397c] --&gt;&lt;div class="jive-rendered-content"&gt;&lt;p&gt;You can make this specific by making a local copy of the ethernetcsmacd template on the device class that you want it to apply to. Then, you go about editing that template ala the instructions above. You can only have the ethernetcsmacd template apply to a device class (it is a component template, which works differently than device templates), not a specific device. If you want it on a specific device, maybe you have to place that device in a seperate sub-device class of its own and put the template there too.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- [DocumentBodyEnd:02d10f05-4469-4c6e-bb9f-cb03efde397c] --&gt;</description>
